# Task 1.01 — Hub-Spoke VNet + Private Endpoints: Walkthrough

## What Was Built

A complete Terraform **networking foundation** for the AI Multi-Tenant Chatbot, organized in a clean root + modules pattern and validated as correct.

## Files Created

| File | Purpose |
|---|---|
| [terraform/main.tf](file:///c:/ANTI/Chat-azure/main-bot/terraform/main.tf) | Root orchestrator — calls `module.networking`, stubs remaining modules |
| [terraform/outputs.tf](file:///c:/ANTI/Chat-azure/main-bot/terraform/outputs.tf) | Root outputs — exposes all VNet/subnet/DNS IDs |
| [terraform/variables.tf](file:///c:/ANTI/Chat-azure/main-bot/terraform/variables.tf) | Root input variables with defaults and validation |
| [terraform/modules/networking/main.tf](file:///c:/ANTI/Chat-azure/main-bot/terraform/modules/networking/main.tf) | Hub-Spoke VNets, subnets, NSGs, Private DNS, peering |
| [terraform/modules/networking/variables.tf](file:///c:/ANTI/Chat-azure/main-bot/terraform/modules/networking/variables.tf) | Module input variables |
| [terraform/modules/networking/outputs.tf](file:///c:/ANTI/Chat-azure/main-bot/terraform/modules/networking/outputs.tf) | Module outputs (IDs used by downstream modules) |
| [terraform/environments/dev.tfvars](file:///c:/ANTI/Chat-azure/main-bot/terraform/environments/dev.tfvars) | Dev-sized overrides |
| [terraform/environments/prod.tfvars](file:///c:/ANTI/Chat-azure/main-bot/terraform/environments/prod.tfvars) | Production-sized overrides |

## Architecture Decisions

- **Hub-Spoke model**: Hub VNet (`10.0.0.0/16`) for shared services + Spoke VNet (`10.1.0.0/16`) for workloads
- **4 dedicated subnets** in Spoke: private-endpoints `/24`, ACA `/23` (or `/21` in prod), APIM `/28`, ACI `/24`
- **7 Private DNS zones** registered: `privatelink.openai.azure.com`, `blob.core.windows.net`, `documents.azure.com`, `search.windows.net`, `vaultcore.azure.net`, `servicebus.windows.net`, `postgres.database.azure.com`
- **NSGs** on each subnet with an explicit `Deny_Internet_Outbound` rule (lowest priority overrider) + ACA infra allow rules
- **VNet peering** bidirectional Hub↔Spoke using `allow_forwarded_traffic = true`
- **Two Resource Groups**: `rg-<project>-<env>-hub` and `rg-<project>-<env>-spoke`

